---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="What this blog is and how it's made"
	pubDate={new Date('March 01 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		I'm a software developer who specializes in frontend UI/UX. I'm comfortable in the browser —
		components, design systems, interactions, all of that. What I'm less comfortable with is
		everything else: networking, hardware, DevOps, backend systems, embedded software. The stuff
		that most frontend developers quietly avoid.
	</p>

	<p>
		This blog is about tackling that stuff anyway. Every post here is a project that was technically
		out of my depth — and how I got through it with AI as a collaborator. Not a shortcut, but a
		force multiplier. I still have to understand the problem, make the decisions, and do the work.
		AI helps me move through unfamiliar territory without getting stuck for days on things that
		aren't the point.
	</p>

	<p>
		That collaboration is transparent here. The code for this site, and a lot of the writing in
		these posts, was produced with AI assistance. I think that's worth being upfront about — both
		because it's honest, and because figuring out how to work well with AI tools is itself one of
		the more interesting problems I'm working on.
	</p>

	<p>
		The ideas, the projects, and the experiences are mine. The help is real.
	</p>
</Layout>
